%% Mermaid diagram: Payment flow (platform vs tenant)

flowchart LR
  A[Client request (initiate payment)] --> B{Is tenantId provided?}
  B -- yes --> C[TENANT context]
  B -- no --> D[LICENSE (platform) context]
  C --> E[PaymentService.getChannel(tenantId, provider)]
  D --> F[PaymentService.getChannel(null, provider)]
  E -->|channel exists| G[Use tenant channel credentials]
  E -->|no channel| H[Return error: No tenant channel configured]
  F -->|channel exists| I[Use platform channel credentials]
  F -->|no channel| J[If LICENSE allowed -> env fallback or error]

  subgraph Webhook processing
    W1[Incoming webhook POST to /api/webhooks/{provider}] --> W2[PaymentService.resolveWebhookChannel]
    W2 --> W3{Enumerate active channels for provider}
    W3 --> W4[Try verifyWebhook() for each channel in isolation]
    W4 -->|match| W5[Resolved channel -> processWebhook scoped to resolved tenantId]
    W4 -->|no match| W6[Log rejected webhook (unverified)]
  end

  style W1 fill:#fff7e6,stroke:#ff9900
